<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

In this posting:
[1] OIE report
[2] News report

******
[1] OIE report
Date: Wed 7 Jul 2010
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly
disease information 2010; 23(27) [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahis/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=9485>


Foot-and-mouth disease, Japan: follow up report no 12
-----------------------------------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 7 Jul 2010 from Dr Toshiro
Kawashima, CVO, Animal Health Division, Ministry of Agriculture,
Forestry and Fisheries, Tokyo, Japan.

Summary
Report type: follow-up report no. 12
Start date: 26 Mar 2010
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 20 Apr 2010
Report date: 7 Jul 2010
Date submitted to OIE: 7 Jul 2010
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: May 2000
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Foot-and-mouth disease virus
Serotype: O
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1: Miyazaki city 3, Miyazaki
Date of start of the outbreak: 4 Jul 2010
Outbreak status: resolved (5 Jul 2010) [by stamping out]
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 16 / 1 / 0 / 16 / 0

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1

Epidemiological comments: movement restrictions around Miyakonojo
city, Hyuga city, and Saito city were lifted on 2, 3, and 6 Jul 2010
respectively.
The absences were demonstrated by serological surveillance targeted
at all susceptible animals kept within 3 km [2 mi] around affected
farms and in epidemiological related farms with them as well as by
clinical surveillance targeted at all susceptible animals in the
areas.
A local government's veterinary service found a cow showed typical
clinical signs of FMD by surveillance on 4 Jul 2010. The affected
farm is in a movement control area around Miyazaki city. All
susceptible animals in the farm were destroyed on 5 Jul 2010.

Control measures
Measures applied: stamping out; quarantine; movement control inside
the country; screening;
Vaccination in response to the outbreak (s):
Administrative division / Species / Total Vaccinated / Details
Miyazaki / Swine / 79 603 / Oil-adjuvant killed vaccine against type O
Miyazaki / Cattle / 45 961 / Oil-adjuvant killed vaccine against type O
Disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s)

--
